properties.documentation: **NOTE: This is an internal NVD schema and should not be published. This schema defines the SP800-53 data feed.
A control as defined in NIST SP 800-53.
The root element of the NVD SP800-53 control data feed. Multiple "control" child elements describe specific controls.

documentation.value: The date the feed was generated.

properties.documentation: Defines a security control as specified in NIST Special Publication SP800-53.

documentation.value: Allocates controls across low-impact, moderate-impact, and high-impact systems as described in Appendix F of SP800-53.
The most general classification of SP800-53 controls. Currently there are three control classes, Management, Technical, Operational
Grouping of controls within a control class based on dominant characterstics of controls in that family.

Unique identifier of the control, consists of a two-character family identifier plus the control number within the family. For example, CP-9 is the ninth control in the Contingency Planning (CP) family.
Recommended priority code used for sequencing decisions during security control implementation as described in Appendix D of SP800-53.
Indicates when a control has been withdrawn.
Provides statements of security capability to build in additional functionality and/or increase the strength of a control as defined by NIST SP 800-70.

properties.documentation: The body of the control, also known as the control section, provides a concise statement of the specific security capabilities needed to protect a particular aspect of an information system.
Provides additional information related to a specific security control, but contains no requirements.

The representation of a control statement.

documentation.value: Unique identifier of the control statement, a concatenation of the Control Number, and any enclosing Control Enhancements and/or statements in which the statement is along with the specific list item for this statment appended.

properties.documentation: The 800-53A objectives for an 800-53 control or control enhancement.
An 800-53A objective.
The decisions associated with the 800-53A objective.
A decision associated with the 800-53A objective. The body of the element contains the description of the decision, encoded as HTML.
A schema element that typically spans multiple sentences and paragraphs.
The potential assessments associated with the 800-53A objective.
A potential assessment associated with the 800-53A objective.

documentation.value: An object for this potential assessment.
A collection of one or more locale specific reference items.

properties.documentation: Type for a locale specific reference with an optional URI reference. This would normally be used to point to extra descriptive material, or the supplier's web site, or the platform documentation. It consists of a piece of text (intended to be human-readable) and a URI (intended to be a URL, and point to a real resource).
A collection of one or more references.

Distinguishes between low-impact, moderate-impact, and high-impact systems.
Priority of controls useful in sequencing decisions.
